ENGLISH: We have begun the process of joining NATO
Joining the NATO

We have begun the process of joining the NATO as a member state. Whether we are permitted into the organisation at this time or not will depend on the opinions held by theNATO's Permanent Members.\nThrough the NATO we hope to gain a voice on the international diplomatic stage, shape the creation of new international law, and benefit from the collective security the organisation provides.\n
Okay
A New NATO Member?

$FROMCOUNTRY$ has begun the process of joining the NATO as a member state. As a NATO Permanent Member we have the option of vetoing this application but doing so would come at the cost of some of our international prestige.
Veto
Don't Veto
NATO Application Vetoed
$FROMCOUNTRY$, that is a NATO Permanent Member state has chosen to veto our current application to the NATO. We will be able to attempt this process again in two years time.
Unfortunate
NATO Application Progresses

None of the NATOPermanent Member states have chosen to veto our application to the NATO and thus our membership application will now move forward through the NATO's legal processes by being forwarded to the Secretary General.
Good things take time.
Admitted to the NATO
We have recieved word that the NATO Security Council has formally accepted our application to join the NATO as a member state. We can now fully participate in the organisation.
Good news
NATO Membership Application

$FROMCOUNTRY$ has begun the process of joining the NATO, and has not had its application vetoed by any of the NATO's Permanent Members.\nAs the current Secretary General of the NATO we will now progress this application through the relevant legal processes, although we may have the option of fast-tracking it.
Fast track the process
Let the process run its course
